        jLabel32.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Tahoma", 0, 12));
        jLabel32.setText("<html>\n<b>Biogenesis:</b> The idea that life can only arise from pre-existing life<br>\n<b>Heterotroph hypothesis:</b> No atmosphere on Earth.  Random chemical reactions gave rise to anaerobes which increased carbon dioxide in the atmosphere, this allowed for photosynthetic organisms to develop which then added oxygen<br>\n \n\n  <b>   Lamarck’s Theory:</b> The more an organ is used, the bigger and more developed it becomes; the less an organ is used, the small and less developed it becomes. There exists ability to pass on traits obtained during lifetime<br>\n<b>    Darwin’s Theory:</b><br>\n\n                                                             i.      Overproduction<br>\n                                                          ii.      Competition<br>\n                                                       iii.      Variation<br>\n                                                        iv.      Adaptation of any trait that improves an organisms chance for survival and reproduction<br>\n                                                           v.      Natural Selection<br>\n                                                        vi.      Speciation<br>\n</html>");
        jLabel32.setVerticalAlignment(javax.swing.SwingConstants.TOP);
        jLabel32.setBorder(javax.swing.BorderFactory.createTitledBorder(null, "Theories", javax.swing.border.TitledBorder.DEFAULT_JUSTIFICATION, javax.swing.border.TitledBorder.DEFAULT_POSITION, new java.awt.Font("AR CENA", 0, 24))); // NOI18N
        jPanel10.add(jLabel32, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(10, 0, 320, 350));

        jLabel33.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Tahoma", 0, 12));
        jLabel33.setText("<html>\n<b>Types of Adaptations:</b><br>\n(i)Structural-Involving the body of the organism<br>\n(ii)Physiological-Involving the metabolism of the organism<br><br>\n<b> Reason for Adaptation:</b><br>\n1.    Increasing ability to obtain food<br>\n2.    Increasing chance of reproduction<br>\n3.    Increasing ability to avoid predators<br>\na.     Camouflage<br>\nb.     Warning Coloration and Mimicry<br><br>\n     \n<b> Types of Natural Selection:</b><br>\n\n(i) Direction<br>\n(ii) Stabilizing<br>\n(iii)Disruptive\n</html>");
        jLabel33.setBorder(javax.swing.BorderFactory.createTitledBorder(null, "Adaptation and Natural Selection", javax.swing.border.TitledBorder.DEFAULT_JUSTIFICATION, javax.swing.border.TitledBorder.DEFAULT_POSITION, new java.awt.Font("AR CENA", 0, 24))); // NOI18N
        jPanel10.add(jLabel33, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(10, 360, 320, 290));

        jLabel34.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Tahoma", 0, 12));
        jLabel34.setHorizontalAlignment(javax.swing.SwingConstants.CENTER);
        jLabel34.setText("<html><b>Speciation:</b> The formation of a new , when species lose the ability to interbreed<br><br>\n     <b> Isolation:</b>Anything that prevents two groups within a species from interbreeding\n will lead to enough of a difference that reproduction between groups will no longer occur\nUsually two stages- <br>\na.     Geographic Isolation<br>\nb.     Reproductive Isolation<br><br>\n\n\n<b>Adaptive Radiation:</b>.As organisms radiate (spread out) they must adapt to new environments; hence they will develop differences which may cause speciation.<br><br>\n\n \n<b>  Convergent Evolution:</b>Non related species may evolve to appear very similar to one another even though they are not related.<br><br>\n<b>Co-evolution:</b>  Non related species may effect one another’s evolution as they evolve in response to one another.Eg:Flowers and bees.\n\n</html>\n");
        jLabel34.setVerticalAlignment(javax.swing.SwingConstants.TOP);
        jLabel34.setBorder(javax.swing.BorderFactory.createTitledBorder(null, "Terminology", javax.swing.border.TitledBorder.DEFAULT_JUSTIFICATION, javax.swing.border.TitledBorder.DEFAULT_POSITION, new java.awt.Font("AR CENA", 0, 24))); // NOI18N
        jPanel10.add(jLabel34, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(750, 0, 330, 370));

        jLabel35.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Tahoma", 0, 12));
        jLabel35.setText("<html>\n\n                                                          <b>     Homologous structures:</b>-Similar structure, different function<br><br>\n<b>     Analogous structures:</b>     -Similar function, different structure<br><br>\n \n \n<b>     Vestigial structures: </b>Remnants of structures that were functional in ancestral forms<br><br>\n\n<b>     Embryological Similarities:</b> Similarities in fetal development<br><br>\n\n<b>    Molecular Similarities:</b>      DNA as evidence. More similar sequences indicate relationships\n\n\n</html>");
        jLabel35.setVerticalAlignment(javax.swing.SwingConstants.TOP);
        jLabel35.setBorder(javax.swing.BorderFactory.createTitledBorder(null, "Evidences Of Evolution", javax.swing.border.TitledBorder.DEFAULT_JUSTIFICATION, javax.swing.border.TitledBorder.DEFAULT_POSITION, new java.awt.Font("AR CENA", 0, 24))); // NOI18N
        jPanel10.add(jLabel35, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(750, 380, 330, 260));

